While building [``pyramid_swagger``](https://travis-ci.org/macisamuele/pyramid_swagger/builds/271496637) I got a list of tests failure related to `` KeyError: 'x-model'`` in [``bravado_core. spec_flattening .flattened_spec``](https://github.com/Yelp/bravado-core/blob/v4.8.3/bravado_core/spec_flattening.py#L303-L306).

Minimal example to reproduce the issue:
- ``swagger.json``
```json
{
  "swagger": "2.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "Test",
    "version": "1.0"
  },
  "paths": {},
  "definitions": {
    "object": {
      "properties": {
        "property": {
          "$ref": "aux.json#/definitions/referenced_object"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
- ``aux.json``
```json
{
    "definitions": {
        "referenced_object": {
            "type": "object"
        }
    }
}
```
- ``test.py``
```python
import json
from os.path import abspath
from bravado_core.spec import Spec

root_swagger_path = abspath('swagger.json')
with open(root_swagger_path) as f:
    spec_dict = json.load(f)

spec = Spec.from_dict(spec_dict, origin_url='file://{}'.format(root_swagger_path))
spec.flattened_spec
```
Running ``test.py`` generates the following traceback
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "test.py", line 10, in <module>
    spec.flattened_spec
  File "/Users/maci/pg/bravado-core/.tox/py35/lib/python3.5/site-packages/bravado_core/spec.py", line 305, in flattened_spec
    spec_definitions=self.definitions,
  File "/Users/maci/pg/bravado-core/.tox/py35/lib/python3.5/site-packages/bravado_core/spec_flattening.py", line 305, in flattened_spec
    for definition in itervalues(known_mappings['definitions'])
  File "/Users/maci/pg/bravado-core/.tox/py35/lib/python3.5/site-packages/bravado_core/spec_flattening.py", line 305, in <setcomp>
    for definition in itervalues(known_mappings['definitions'])
KeyError: 'x-model'
```

The issue is caused by the wrong assumption that definitions are tagged as model (have ``x-model`` property).

To fix this we could:
1. make sure that ``flattened_spec`` does not assume that ``x-model`` will always be present
2. improve models tagging (currently ``tag_models`` tags only schema objects on ``/definition`` of the root swagger specs file

NOTE: the second approach requires more time, so I would suggest to go with point 1 first

